traxIdTable.name: traxIdTable
traxIdTable.description: A table that contains information that identifies the hardware and software that make up the specified Hiper TRAX card.

traxIdEntry.name: traxIdEntry
traxIdEntry.description: There is one entry in this table for every Hiper TRAX card in the chassis.

traxIdIndex.name: traxIdIndex
traxIdIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies the Hiper TRAX card for which this row in the table pertains. The value of this index matches the value of the index for the corresponding entity in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

traxIdHardwareSerNum.name: traxIdHardwareSerNum
traxIdHardwareSerNum.description: The Hiper TRAX card's hardware serial number as stored in EEPROM.

traxIdHardwareRev.name: traxIdHardwareRev
traxIdHardwareRev.description: The hardware revision of the specified Hiper TRAX card as stored in its EEPROM.

traxIdSoftwareRev.name: traxIdSoftwareRev
traxIdSoftwareRev.description: The revision of the software being executed in the specified Hiper TRAX card.

traxIdCpuType.name: traxIdCpuType
traxIdCpuType.description: Defines the type of CPU present on the Hiper TRAX NAC.

traxIdRamInstalled.name: traxIdRamInstalled
traxIdRamInstalled.description: Specifies the amount of DRAM installed on the Hiper TRAX Gateway NAC in Kbytes.

traxIdFlashInstalled.name: traxIdFlashInstalled
traxIdFlashInstalled.description: Specifies the amount of Flash Rom installed on the Hiper TRAX NAC in Kbytes.

traxIdSelfTestResult.name: traxIdSelfTestResult
traxIdSelfTestResult.description: Displays the results of the most resent self test performed by the Hiper TRAX NAC. If all tests have passed a value of 0 is returned.

traxIdMgmtConnect.name: traxIdMgmtConnect
traxIdMgmtConnect.description: Indicates the current status of Hiper TRAX Card user interface.

traxCmdTable.name: traxCmdTable
traxCmdTable.description: The Hiper TRAX Card Command table contains an entry for each of the manageable Hiper TRAX Cards in the chassis. It provides a means through which to take specific actions on one or more Hiper TRAX cards in the NAS chassis.

traxCmdEntry.name: traxCmdEntry
traxCmdEntry.description: There is one Hiper TRAX Card Command entry per Hiper TRAX Card in the chassis.

traxCmdIndex.name: traxCmdIndex
traxCmdIndex.description: A unique value for each Hiper TRAX Card in the chassis. The value of this object matches the value of the index of the corresponding Hiper TRAX Card's entry in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

traxCmdMgtStationId.name: traxCmdMgtStationId
traxCmdMgtStationId.description: This object is a generic read-write variable that a Management Station (MS) can use to guarantee that the results from a given command are the results of a command issued by that specific MS. Each MS must SET a unique value to this object

traxCmdReqId.name: traxCmdReqId
traxCmdReqId.description: This object contains the value of the request-id field in the SNMP PDU which invoked the current or most recent command or test on this X.25 Card. If the request-id is unknown or undefined, this object contains the value zero.

traxCmdFunction.name: traxCmdFunction
traxCmdFunction.description: This object contains a value which describes the command which is being invoked.

traxCmdForce.name: traxCmdForce
traxCmdForce.description: In some cases, the Hiper TRAX Card may be in a state such that certain commands could adversely affect connections. In such cases, a command request with this object not present or set to noForce will result in a warning

traxCmdParam.name: traxCmdParam
traxCmdParam.description: This object contains parameters that are specific to the particular command being issued. In some cases, there will be no aditional parameters required.

traxCmdResult.name: traxCmdResult
traxCmdResult.description: This object contains the result of the most recently requested command or test, or the value none(1) if no commands have been requested since the last reset.

traxCmdCode.name: traxCmdCode
traxCmdCode.description: The value of this object is noError(1) if the command was successful, and indicates a further description of what went wrong if it was unsuccessful.

traxCfgIndex.description: A unique value for each Hiper TRAX NAC installed in the chassis. The value of this index is identical to the index in the USR chassis MIB associates with the Hiper TRAX Card entity.
